    <text id="R1511057T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this June, 1863, dispatch, Union Staff officer Donn Platt writes Captain
                    William H. Boyd, stationed at Chambersburg, with orders to move his cavalry
                    troops.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. MIDDLE DEPARTMENT, EIGHTH ARMY CORPS
                    <name type="recipient">Capt. WILLIAM H. BOYD,<lb/> First New York Cavalry,
                        Chambersburg, Pa.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-06-15">June 15, 1863.</date>
                        <name type="place">Baltimore</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>You will immediately proceed with your command, together with all other cavalry
                    from this department that may have arrived at Chambersburg, and go by way of
                    Emmitsburg and Frederick to Harper's Ferry, there to report to Brig.-Gen. Tyler
                    for duty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>By order of Maj.-Gen. Schenck:</salute>
                    <signed>DONN PLATT,<lb/> Chief of Staff.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
